 "callout": "<b>Why this sits alongside the GA4 dashboard.</b> GA4 is becoming steadily less reliable as cookie consent and privacy tracking cut what it can see, so treat it as a guide to overall website performance rather than a count of bookings. It only fires for bookings made on our own website, so it cannot see <b>OpenRice</b>, only partly captures <b>Google Reserve</b>, and never sees walk-ins or the reception desks, which together are over 40% of Hong Kong covers. GA4 reads <b>\u25b27.3% YoY</b> while total covers created are <b>+18% YoY</b>. Read this as the fuller demand and channel picture, not as a contradiction of GA4."
